6
00:01:36.137 --> 00:01:38.567
I expect to get paid extra even if you're 10 minutes late.

7
00:01:38.567 --> 00:01:40.007
And I don't work on weekends.

8
00:01:40.007 --> 00:01:42.408
If you want a premium service such as baby massages...

9
00:01:42.408 --> 00:01:46.048
and premium baby food, you need to pay 300 dollars more.

10
00:01:46.347 --> 00:01:48.278
Do you have any questions?

11
00:01:49.918 --> 00:01:52.347
- We'll go broke if we are late... - Don't.

12
00:01:52.347 --> 00:01:54.418
Should I ask her? No?

13
00:01:57.487 --> 00:01:59.587
If I get off work early, will I get a discount?

14
00:02:01.358 --> 00:02:03.627
My goodness, I didn't know you guys were married.

15
00:02:04.727 --> 00:02:07.498
My gosh, I guess you really weren't homeless after all.

16
00:02:09.837 --> 00:02:12.438
Then what about that other kid? Was that your second child?

17
00:02:14.337 --> 00:02:15.337
Is this your second marriage?

18
00:02:16.578 --> 00:02:18.608
Did you have an affair?

19
00:02:19.207 --> 00:02:21.248
My goodness, I guess that must be it.

20
00:02:22.018 --> 00:02:23.218
Did they really have an affair?

21
00:02:23.877 --> 00:02:24.948
My goodness.

22
00:02:25.847 --> 00:02:28.787
- Goodbye. - See you at our aerobics class!

23
00:02:28.858 --> 00:02:30.257
- Bye! - Goodbye.

24
00:02:31.257 --> 00:02:32.287
Did you recommend her, Mom?

25
00:02:32.757 --> 00:02:33.828
This is absurd.

26
00:02:35.158 --> 00:02:36.358
My gosh, this is exhausting.

27
00:02:38.168 --> 00:02:40.698
It's so hard to get a babysitter.

28
00:02:40.867 --> 00:02:42.198
What are you going to do? Your hospital is going to open soon.

29
00:02:42.198 --> 00:02:45.108
I'll leave her at the daycare center until 3pm.

30
00:02:45.467 --> 00:02:46.707
Then I'll just have to bring her to my office.

31
00:02:46.937 --> 00:02:50.138
By the way, how do you know all those women?

32
00:02:50.378 --> 00:02:51.478
How about you?

33
00:02:52.448 --> 00:02:53.578
I don't even want to talk about it.

34
00:02:58.647 --> 00:02:59.747
Ha Ri.

35
00:03:00.418 --> 00:03:01.858
What are you going to do now?

36
00:03:01.918 --> 00:03:04.217
Why don't you help me prepare some stuff for the opening?

37
00:03:04.628 --> 00:03:06.087
How about we have some fun?

38
00:03:07.557 --> 00:03:10.728
Don't even think about it and pay me if you want my service.

39
00:03:11.828 --> 00:03:12.967
It was worth a try.

40
00:03:15.798 --> 00:03:16.937
Hello.

41
00:03:16.997 --> 00:03:18.407
Good to see you.

42
00:03:18.608 --> 00:03:20.138
This is our schedule for the day.

43
00:03:21.508 --> 00:03:22.907
(10am: I Sang and Ha Ri: My Child's First Friend of the Opposite Sex)

44
00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:25.508
(10am: I Sang and Ha Ri: My Child's First Friend of the Opposite Sex)

45
00:03:26.277 --> 00:03:27.407
Ms. Jang has a photoshoot?

46
00:03:27.647 --> 00:03:29.448
She takes her job very seriously.

47
00:03:29.717 --> 00:03:32.848
Her suspension only means that she needs to stay clear of her boss.

48
00:03:34.888 --> 00:03:36.018
Good morning.

49
00:03:48.598 --> 00:03:49.737
What's the photoshoot for?

50
00:03:51.707 --> 00:03:52.807
Don't be so obvious.

51
00:04:01.478 --> 00:04:03.117
It's an article on children having friends of the opposite sex.

52
00:04:07.048 --> 00:04:09.187
My gosh, you startled me.

53
00:04:09.318 --> 00:04:11.527
- What gives? - I'm sorry about that.

54
00:04:12.858 --> 00:04:15.027
This isn't your photoshoot though.

55
00:04:15.298 --> 00:04:17.157
I told Ha Ri to stay home...

56
00:04:17.157 --> 00:04:18.927
since I could manage this myself.

57
00:04:20.798 --> 00:04:24.038
It's a monthly series of ours, so Sang Hee knows what to do.

58
00:04:26.407 --> 00:04:28.608
Would she be in the mood to work when she was suspended?

59
00:04:29.337 --> 00:04:31.807
I told her to stay well away from this place.

60
00:04:36.617 --> 00:04:38.318
That's unnecessary camaraderie.

61
00:04:39.888 --> 00:04:43.288
- Sorry? - What kind of photos do you need?

62
00:04:43.518 --> 00:04:44.987
Unbelievable...

63
00:04:45.328 --> 00:04:48.128
I want the two of them shot from the front...

64
00:04:48.497 --> 00:04:50.527
- but leave some space up top. - Gosh.

65
00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:52.268
I see right through you.

66
00:04:52.568 --> 00:04:54.797
Please leave some space up top for the title.

67
00:04:55.268 --> 00:04:56.368
I heard you.

68
00:04:59.568 --> 00:05:03.337
- Just a bit more... - I'll adjust as we go.

69
00:05:09.748 --> 00:05:13.417
(Episode 5: When We Wish to Believe in Fate)

70
00:05:21.857 --> 00:05:22.957
Mom.

71
00:05:24.698 --> 00:05:27.568
Hold on. What brings you by?

72
00:05:30.998 --> 00:05:33.238
- Hello, sir. - Hi.

73
00:05:40.347 --> 00:05:41.518
Here you go.

74
00:05:42.647 --> 00:05:44.847
Why are you treating me like a patient?

75
00:05:45.047 --> 00:05:46.748
Because you are.

76
00:05:46.847 --> 00:05:49.157
You should stick to food that is easy to digest.

77
00:05:54.628 --> 00:05:55.797
Gosh.

78
00:05:56.758 --> 00:05:58.467
Are you aiming to be a professional guitarist?

79
00:05:58.467 --> 00:06:00.167
You shouldn't play in this condition of yours.

80
00:06:00.597 --> 00:06:02.597
My sore wrist goes back to my days working in diners.

81
00:06:03.068 --> 00:06:06.707
I can't believe the pain is back after a few guitar strokes.

82
00:06:07.738 --> 00:06:10.907
Don't overexert yourself. It's just a stupid guitar.

83
00:06:11.748 --> 00:06:13.678
It isn't for me.

84
00:06:14.147 --> 00:06:18.087
Playing "Spanish Romance" has been a lifelong dream of mine.

85
00:06:18.488 --> 00:06:19.787
Your father distracted me though,

86
00:06:19.787 --> 00:06:21.888
so I was only able to manage "Edelweiss".

87
00:06:22.587 --> 00:06:25.558
Darn it. When you fall for someone,

88
00:06:25.558 --> 00:06:28.328
you tend to fall hard.

89
00:06:31.628 --> 00:06:34.097
Luck seems to have found you in your later years though.

90
00:06:34.097 --> 00:06:36.097
Your cancer was detected in the early stages...

91
00:06:36.097 --> 00:06:39.008
and you have enough money to do what you want in your life.

92
00:06:39.238 --> 00:06:41.308
That doesn't mean a thing to me...

93
00:06:41.607 --> 00:06:43.277
because my body isn't what it used to be.

94
00:06:43.777 --> 00:06:46.777
How great would it be to do everything I missed out on...

95
00:06:46.777 --> 00:06:49.777
when I had to work hard to keep food on the table?

96
00:06:53.748 --> 00:06:54.888
Exactly.

97
00:06:55.917 --> 00:06:57.758
We all should do what we want in life.

98
00:06:58.258 --> 00:07:00.688
It's why I want to give birth to a child.

99
00:07:00.957 --> 00:07:02.797
I'm not producing enough eggs...

100
00:07:02.897 --> 00:07:05.568
and my chances of pregnancy will only get slimmer...

101
00:07:05.568 --> 00:07:06.967
once I receive surgery for my endometriosis.

102
00:07:13.467 --> 00:07:14.878
It's nothing serious though.

103
00:07:19.777 --> 00:07:20.878
Wait.

104
00:07:22.217 --> 00:07:23.417
Was that about you?

105
00:07:26.147 --> 00:07:27.847
I can have the baby...

106
00:07:27.847 --> 00:07:29.488
and receive surgery for endometriosis.

107
00:07:29.488 --> 00:07:30.717
It's nothing.

108
00:07:30.957 --> 00:07:33.957
Now eat up before it gets cold.

109
00:07:34.628 --> 00:07:35.797
Come on.

110
00:07:36.157 --> 00:07:37.397
There you go.

111
00:07:42.738 --> 00:07:44.967
You want to go through IVF on your own?

112
00:07:44.967 --> 00:07:46.938
Did I misunderstand that or are you insane?

113
00:07:47.068 --> 00:07:48.738
I told you I was done wanting a marriage.

114
00:07:49.378 --> 00:07:50.578
I'd rather have a kid instead.

115
00:07:51.448 --> 00:07:53.578
You really are insane, aren't you?

116
00:07:53.578 --> 00:07:55.477
People will constantly judge me for this,

117
00:07:55.777 --> 00:07:57.378
so can you at least be on my side?

118
00:07:57.647 --> 00:08:00.318
I'm all on board with you buying green onions.

119
00:08:00.318 --> 00:08:03.258
But how can I support you when it's sperms you want to buy?

120
00:08:05.157 --> 00:08:06.558
I'm not buying anything.

121
00:08:07.488 --> 00:08:09.058
It'll be consensual.

122
00:08:09.558 --> 00:08:10.628
And keep your voice down.

123
00:08:12.527 --> 00:08:15.438
My friend, Ha Ri, I strongly am against this idea.

124
00:08:15.438 --> 00:08:17.537
- Well, I think it's perfect. - Wait.

125
00:08:19.268 --> 00:08:22.078
So you're seriously thinking about having this baby?

126
00:08:22.477 --> 00:08:25.378
On your own when it's hard enough to raise a child with a partner?

127
00:08:26.078 --> 00:08:28.448
Fine. Let's say that it's doable.

128
00:08:28.547 --> 00:08:31.347
What if a decent man comes your way?

129
00:08:33.018 --> 00:08:35.917
I tortured myself with that thought for 20 years.

130
00:08:36.417 --> 00:08:38.957
I'm done trying to meet a husband.

131
00:08:42.097 --> 00:08:44.967
My friend, don't close the door to your options...

132
00:08:45.128 --> 00:08:46.727
and reconsider the men...

133
00:08:46.727 --> 00:08:49.037
that you once dumped or took a pass on.

134
00:08:49.097 --> 00:08:52.438
You'll be surprised by the revelation it could bring you.

135
00:08:52.438 --> 00:08:55.607
Just keep digging, okay? There are many decent men out there.

136
00:08:55.678 --> 00:08:57.378
Like whom? Do you know anyone?

137
00:08:59.948 --> 00:09:01.948
Wait. What about my sister's husband?

138
00:09:02.178 --> 00:09:03.417
As you know,

139
00:09:03.417 --> 00:09:05.748
he makes himself breakfast before going to work,

140
00:09:05.748 --> 00:09:07.248
get the kids to school,

141
00:09:07.248 --> 00:09:08.718
takes the family abroad every year,

142
00:09:08.718 --> 00:09:10.657
and only has eyes for my sister.

143
00:09:10.718 --> 00:09:11.787
I know.

144
00:09:12.557 --> 00:09:14.787
Your brother-in-law is the best.

145
00:09:15.258 --> 00:09:16.397
See?

146
00:09:16.628 --> 00:09:18.468
He must be here to shop with your sister.

147
00:09:19.228 --> 00:09:20.327
That's him, right?

148
00:09:20.797 --> 00:09:22.167
Did your sister lose weight?

149
00:09:22.397 --> 00:09:24.567
Check out her slender figure.

150
00:09:27.508 --> 00:09:28.608
Here.

151
00:09:29.838 --> 00:09:31.547
Who's the young woman?

152
00:09:32.147 --> 00:09:33.277
- Don't wait for me. - What?

153
00:09:34.108 --> 00:09:36.917
Eun Young, take a photo first.

154
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:39.147
As evidence!

155
00:09:40.147 --> 00:09:41.248
Brother-in-law?

156
00:09:45.388 --> 00:09:46.628
Who is this woman?

157
00:09:50.827 --> 00:09:53.567
You have the wrong person.

158
00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:56.838
Hold on. Wait. Stop right there.

159
00:09:57.167 --> 00:09:58.338
Stop!

160
00:09:58.868 --> 00:10:00.108
You have the wrong person.

161
00:10:00.368 --> 00:10:02.537
Oh, dear.

162
00:10:05.677 --> 00:10:07.378
I'm not your brother-in-law.

163
00:10:07.547 --> 00:10:09.047
- Stop! - Darn it.

164
00:10:10.348 --> 00:10:13.888
- I'm not who you think I am. - Stop!

165
00:10:14.388 --> 00:10:15.518
Wait!

166
00:10:16.287 --> 00:10:19.358
- I'm not your brother-in-law. - You are!

167
00:10:19.888 --> 00:10:21.057
I'm not!

168
00:10:24.057 --> 00:10:26.628
Eun Young used to think I was pathetic...

169
00:10:26.628 --> 00:10:28.638
for wanting to get married.

170
00:10:29.238 --> 00:10:30.868
As a successful app developer,

171
00:10:30.868 --> 00:10:32.738
she was on the verge of launching her startup.

172
00:10:33.268 --> 00:10:35.608
She went to an investor for an investment...

173
00:10:36.978 --> 00:10:38.647
and her life got turned upside down.

174
00:10:39.047 --> 00:10:40.677
A sudden attraction...

175
00:10:40.777 --> 00:10:42.947
led to marriage and pregnancy.

176
00:10:43.647 --> 00:10:46.018
Until then, she was confident...

177
00:10:46.018 --> 00:10:47.218
