541
00:35:00.193 --> 00:35:02.522
The journalists and I have been proposing advertisement deals...

542
00:35:02.522 --> 00:35:04.223
just as much as the Advertising Department.

543
00:35:04.263 --> 00:35:06.493
I didn't even take time off to care for my child longer.

544
00:35:06.493 --> 00:35:07.832
You should...

545
00:35:10.062 --> 00:35:11.533
if you're sure you'll be back.

546
00:35:12.462 --> 00:35:15.033
Child-rearing doesn't end with just three months,

547
00:35:15.533 --> 00:35:19.372
so if you don't come back after taking all that time off,

548
00:35:19.712 --> 00:35:21.843
you'll only be costing the company money.

549
00:35:22.243 --> 00:35:25.082
I know, sir. It's why I didn't take time off...

550
00:35:25.082 --> 00:35:26.653
even though I'm entitled to.

551
00:35:27.153 --> 00:35:28.453
You keep suggesting I shouldn't.

552
00:35:31.823 --> 00:35:34.653
Sir, no matter how hard we work,

553
00:35:34.653 --> 00:35:37.993
we can't do anything about the low birthrate or...

554
00:35:37.993 --> 00:35:39.263
Fine.

555
00:35:41.633 --> 00:35:43.062
Anyway,

556
00:35:43.332 --> 00:35:45.633
we were asked to advertise Mureung City.

557
00:35:46.473 --> 00:35:48.033
"The Baby" should take it.

558
00:35:48.602 --> 00:35:50.703
It was originally meant for "The Deco",

559
00:35:50.703 --> 00:35:53.173
but I'm only giving it to you to boost your sales,

560
00:35:53.173 --> 00:35:55.272
so do a good job on it.

561
00:35:55.872 --> 00:35:58.843
If Mureung City is pleased with the outcome,

562
00:35:59.042 --> 00:36:01.613
all the projects from local governments...

563
00:36:02.312 --> 00:36:04.783
will be turned over to "The Baby".

564
00:36:07.053 --> 00:36:09.323
Mr. Joo, my gosh. You were...

565
00:36:09.553 --> 00:36:12.323
only being hard on us to offer us this deal,

566
00:36:12.522 --> 00:36:14.232
but we were too stupid...

567
00:36:14.633 --> 00:36:16.263
to read into your intentions.

568
00:36:16.602 --> 00:36:17.633
Thank you, sir.

569
00:36:20.133 --> 00:36:22.332
It's why being in this position can get lonely.

570
00:36:31.182 --> 00:36:34.453
Seriously? What are you doing here? Go home and have fun.

571
00:36:36.053 --> 00:36:37.752
I don't feel comfortable doing so.

572
00:36:37.923 --> 00:36:39.182
That's your punishment.

573
00:36:39.182 --> 00:36:41.953
I'd rather have fun here while being uncomfortable.

574
00:36:45.223 --> 00:36:48.763
The City of Mureung has asked us to run an advertisement piece.

575
00:36:48.763 --> 00:36:51.133
You'll take the plane there and gather notes for a day.

576
00:36:51.133 --> 00:36:52.962
Other media outlets will be there,

577
00:36:52.962 --> 00:36:56.033
so make sure you come up with a piece...

578
00:36:56.033 --> 00:36:59.443
that blows the minds of the people of Mureung City.

579
00:37:00.073 --> 00:37:01.142
Who wants to go?

580
00:37:03.783 --> 00:37:06.343
My gosh. I covered 15 stories this month.

581
00:37:06.613 --> 00:37:09.153
Well, I'm going to Gangwon Province...

582
00:37:09.153 --> 00:37:10.653
to run a piece on the wholesale warehouse.

583
00:37:10.783 --> 00:37:14.352
Actually, I'd like to ask what our plans are for...

584
00:37:14.553 --> 00:37:16.093
the readers of our first issue.

585
00:37:27.372 --> 00:37:29.533
Ha Ri is terrified to fly.

586
00:37:29.533 --> 00:37:32.573
Exactly. Besides, how can she go when she's been suspended?

587
00:37:32.903 --> 00:37:35.212
She can't since she's out having fun.

588
00:37:41.153 --> 00:37:43.783
Since I've been suspended, I'll write this piece.

589
00:37:46.223 --> 00:37:47.622
I can't go.

590
00:37:48.522 --> 00:37:49.792
Why not?

591
00:37:49.962 --> 00:37:52.763
I made a drunken mistake in front of Ms. Jang.

592
00:37:55.732 --> 00:37:57.033
No way.

593
00:37:59.932 --> 00:38:01.173
You showed her your cute side?

594
00:38:10.542 --> 00:38:11.613
You idiot!

595
00:38:12.743 --> 00:38:15.553
How can you look Ms. Jang in the eyes now?

596
00:38:18.423 --> 00:38:20.392
The embarrassment might just kill me,

597
00:38:21.252 --> 00:38:22.653
but I'll try and hang in there.

598
00:38:23.093 --> 00:38:25.292
The photos are important for this piece...

599
00:38:25.562 --> 00:38:27.892
so they need an expert photographer,

600
00:38:27.892 --> 00:38:29.462
but I busted my arm.

601
00:38:29.732 --> 00:38:31.962
I can't bring in the money with a busted arm...

602
00:38:32.232 --> 00:38:33.703
which means I can't hire a freelancer.

603
00:38:33.973 --> 00:38:35.203
Unbelievable.

604
00:38:35.533 --> 00:38:38.243
- I'll have to give up the studio. - That's enough.

605
00:38:38.243 --> 00:38:40.013
I can't look Ms. Jang in the eyes anymore.

606
00:38:42.042 --> 00:38:43.343
This is all on you now!

607
00:38:50.323 --> 00:38:53.522
Mr. Nam, the photographer hasn't contacted me yet.

608
00:38:53.792 --> 00:38:55.392
Don't tell me you still haven't hired one.

609
00:38:55.453 --> 00:38:57.093
He'll be there somewhere.

610
00:38:57.323 --> 00:38:59.892
He's your partner, so look around.

611
00:39:00.633 --> 00:39:02.693
What? My partner?

612
00:39:03.232 --> 00:39:04.232
What the...

613
00:39:09.133 --> 00:39:10.303
I found him.

614
00:39:29.223 --> 00:39:30.323
Shall we?

615
00:39:30.723 --> 00:39:33.593
Why didn't you call to say you were joining me?

616
00:39:34.162 --> 00:39:35.633
We could've carpooled.

617
00:39:36.803 --> 00:39:38.832
- Do you want this? - No.

618
00:39:40.133 --> 00:39:42.772
How about buttered squid or beef jerky?

619
00:39:42.973 --> 00:39:44.142
I'm good.

620
00:39:46.142 --> 00:39:48.073
How about we grab a drink afterward?

621
00:39:48.173 --> 00:39:50.843
I like how alcohol makes you cute and sincere.

622
00:39:50.912 --> 00:39:52.343
Can't I do as I please?

623
00:39:52.682 --> 00:39:54.013
Yes.

624
00:39:54.013 --> 00:39:55.582
Correct.

625
00:39:58.022 --> 00:39:59.122
This isn't a vacation, you know.

626
00:39:59.582 --> 00:40:01.453
But it's still a trip.

627
00:40:01.723 --> 00:40:04.723
What's so bad about buying snacks and getting in the mood?

628
00:40:05.363 --> 00:40:06.622
We're even getting on a plane.

629
00:40:08.863 --> 00:40:10.863
Unbelievable. I hate planes.

630
00:40:15.073 --> 00:40:17.843
But we're not going...

631
00:40:17.843 --> 00:40:20.042
on a vacation though.

632
00:40:20.343 --> 00:40:22.573
So you don't want any snacks?

633
00:40:28.412 --> 00:40:29.982
Isn't that a bit too much?

634
00:40:37.792 --> 00:40:39.763
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.

635
00:40:40.332 --> 00:40:42.932
We welcome you on our flight.

636
00:40:43.432 --> 00:40:46.432
The flight attendants are here to make sure you have...

637
00:40:46.432 --> 00:40:47.973
- a safe journey. - Are you all right?

638
00:40:49.073 --> 00:40:51.943
I just get nervous before the plane takes off.

639
00:40:51.943 --> 00:40:54.073
I'll be fine once we're in the air.

640
00:40:56.212 --> 00:40:57.982
You're not sick or anything, right?

641
00:40:57.982 --> 00:40:58.982
- I'm good. - Thank you for...

642
00:40:58.982 --> 00:41:02.153
your cooperation and we hope...

643
00:42:10.252 --> 00:42:11.383
Hello.

644
00:42:11.383 --> 00:42:12.923
- Hello. - Hello.

645
00:42:16.693 --> 00:42:18.823
Did Ha Ri not come with you?

646
00:42:18.892 --> 00:42:21.693
Ha Ri went on a business trip to Mureung City with Mr. Han.

647
00:42:22.863 --> 00:42:25.332
To that very far city of Mureung...

648
00:42:25.562 --> 00:42:29.102
alone with Mr. Han, with no other staff members.

649
00:42:32.573 --> 00:42:33.712
They went together.

650
00:42:35.812 --> 00:42:38.443
What are they doing there, that they went...

651
00:42:39.142 --> 00:42:40.212
by themselves?

652
00:42:40.912 --> 00:42:43.582
What a load of crock.

653
00:42:47.252 --> 00:42:50.693
Ladies and gentlemen, the pilot has turned off the seat belt sign.

654
00:42:51.093 --> 00:42:54.133
However, because there may be turbulence,

655
00:42:54.133 --> 00:42:57.033
please keep your seat belts on when you are seated.

656
00:42:57.763 --> 00:43:00.062
When the seat belt light is on,

657
00:43:00.062 --> 00:43:03.673
we will not be serving food and beverages for safety reasons.

658
00:43:05.142 --> 00:43:06.843
- Oh dear. - Oh my gosh.

659
00:43:07.142 --> 00:43:08.743
Are you okay, sir?

660
00:44:01.732 --> 00:44:03.832
Maybe he could be the one...

661
00:44:05.033 --> 00:44:06.102
Is it him?

662
00:44:07.173 --> 00:44:08.573
The bus that I missed.

663
00:44:10.443 --> 00:44:11.502
This always happens.

664
00:44:11.642 --> 00:44:13.073
Especially when I'm late for an important appointment,

665
00:44:13.173 --> 00:44:15.073
the bus won't show up.

666
00:44:15.872 --> 00:44:19.212
If I hop in a cab to save time, we get stuck in traffic,

667
00:44:19.582 --> 00:44:22.013
and the bus I was waiting for...

668
00:44:22.013 --> 00:44:24.182
speeds along in the bus express lane.

669
00:44:25.383 --> 00:44:27.392
If my impatience took control,

670
00:44:27.392 --> 00:44:29.792
and made me miss a destined meeting,

671
00:44:31.522 --> 00:44:32.693
will I...

672
00:44:33.863 --> 00:44:37.133
regret not holding his hand later on?

673
00:44:52.542 --> 00:44:55.812
Why won't this open?

674
00:44:56.482 --> 00:44:57.622
Gosh.

675
00:44:59.352 --> 00:45:00.522
It opened easily.

676
00:45:01.022 --> 00:45:02.792
They made it well. You know...

677
00:45:04.022 --> 00:45:06.622
- Do you want this? - No.

678
00:45:07.133 --> 00:45:08.193
Okay.

679
00:45:11.403 --> 00:45:12.633
Sir.

680
00:45:16.903 --> 00:45:18.002
Thank you.

681
00:45:21.113 --> 00:45:23.982
I was giving you my handkerchief, not my hand.

682
00:45:25.082 --> 00:45:27.812
Yes, handkerchief.

683
00:45:37.022 --> 00:45:38.462
- What? - Hey, Ha Ri.

684
00:45:38.763 --> 00:45:40.892
Should I keep my lab coat on or take it off?

685
00:45:41.792 --> 00:45:43.562
Why are you asking me about you taking clothes off?

686
00:45:44.962 --> 00:45:47.173
- Ask the reporter there. - What?

687
00:45:47.932 --> 00:45:49.203
Both look good?

688
00:45:49.272 --> 00:45:51.203
Stop joking around. You're embarrassing me.

689
00:45:51.473 --> 00:45:53.973
Okay. Should I take the pictures with or without?

690
00:45:53.973 --> 00:45:55.743
Take it off if you want. I don't care.

691
00:45:56.743 --> 00:45:57.812
Gosh.

692
00:45:58.542 --> 00:45:59.943
It's better with it on?

693
00:46:00.283 --> 00:46:02.453
Okay, got it. Work hard.

694
00:46:03.513 --> 00:46:04.852
She says I look good with it on.

695
00:46:04.982 --> 00:46:06.653
Okay.

696
00:46:08.193 --> 00:46:09.252
Gosh.

697
00:46:11.662 --> 00:46:14.133
- Was that Dr. Yoon Jae Young? - Yes.

698
00:46:19.803 --> 00:46:21.033
What is it this time?

699
00:46:21.133 --> 00:46:23.473
Should I sit or stand for the picture?

700
00:46:23.943 --> 00:46:27.212
It would be better standing by the window looking cool. right?

701
00:46:27.212 --> 00:46:30.482
It'll bet better seated at my desk so that my nameplate shows.

702
00:46:31.682 --> 00:46:33.013
Sit for the photo...

703
00:46:33.312 --> 00:46:34.453
and cover your gut.

704
00:46:37.823 --> 00:46:40.752
Sure, got it. Okay. Work hard.

705
00:46:43.693 --> 00:46:44.792
Let's start.

706
00:46:51.962 --> 00:46:53.602
What? Why? What? What?

707
00:46:53.602 --> 00:46:55.732
Should I smile or not?

708
00:46:55.732 --> 00:46:57.303
It's best not smiling, right?

709
00:46:57.303 --> 00:46:59.642
To look serious and professional.

710
00:46:59.943 --> 00:47:01.743
No. Smiling may be better.

711
00:47:01.743 --> 00:47:03.312
This is a local hospital.

712
00:47:03.312 --> 00:47:06.113
So it'll be better to look friendly.

713
00:47:06.312 --> 00:47:08.883
Just shut your trap and take the picture, you punk.

714
00:47:14.122 --> 00:47:15.193
Okay.

715
00:47:15.193 --> 00:47:17.522
I look great both ways? What?

716
00:47:17.923 --> 00:47:19.723
Enough, Ha Ri.

717
00:47:26.432 --> 00:47:27.533
Doctor.

718
00:47:29.533 --> 00:47:31.173
It'll be this big.

719
00:47:33.203 --> 00:47:34.973
(My child whines if I don't let her watch on my smartphone.)

720
00:47:37.283 --> 00:47:38.412
That won't be easy.

721
00:47:39.843 --> 00:47:42.412
Mureung is named that because there are no royal tombs.

722
00:47:42.412 --> 00:47:44.522
In order to hide the location of the kings' graves,

723
00:47:44.852 --> 00:47:47.022
they built fake graves here.

724
00:47:47.022 --> 00:47:49.593
There is a legend that a dragon rose from there.

725
00:47:49.823 --> 00:47:51.962
So the saying goes.

726
00:47:53.093 --> 00:47:55.162
- Take all the pictures you want. - Thank you.

727
00:47:58.562 --> 00:47:59.803
Should I take some that way?

728
00:48:01.303 --> 00:48:02.303
I think it'll look good.

729
00:48:04.002 --> 00:48:05.102
Here.

730
00:48:05.403 --> 00:48:06.473
Excuse me.

731
00:48:30.903 --> 00:48:32.062
- Okay, good. - Good?

732
00:48:34.272 --> 00:48:35.372
Shall we go?

733
00:48:38.443 --> 00:48:42.312
Okay. The official schedule for the day is over.

734
00:48:42.312 --> 00:48:44.082
Feel free to take more pictures.

735
00:48:44.283 --> 00:48:46.912
If you want to hang out more, feel free to do that as well.

736
00:48:47.142 --> 00:48:48.812
Thank you, everyone.

737
00:48:48.812 --> 00:48:49.982
- Thank you. - Sure.

738
00:48:53.352 --> 00:48:56.752
Ha Ri. Don't you think we need something better for the main shot?

739
00:48:56.953 --> 00:48:59.993
Right? Should we take some pictures of the sunset?

740
00:49:06.803 --> 00:49:08.533
Is Ha Ri not back yet?

741
00:49:08.903 --> 00:49:11.203
She went to Mureung. She'll probably be home late.

742
00:49:11.272 --> 00:49:12.903
- Come eat. - Auntie.

743
00:49:13.343 --> 00:49:14.613
The photographer is a man.

744
00:49:14.712 --> 00:49:16.712
What if something happens while they're alone together?

745
00:49:17.812 --> 00:49:18.912
Like what?

746
00:49:20.513 --> 00:49:21.682
Something frightening.

747
00:49:29.093 --> 00:49:32.792
I wonder if we needed to rent a car just to go take one picture.

748
00:49:33.562 --> 00:49:35.593
You said your pride is on the line.

749
00:49:36.593 --> 00:49:38.062
It'll say, "Photo by Han I Sang."

750
00:49:38.662 --> 00:49:40.102
So my pride is on the line too.

751
00:49:41.102 --> 00:49:42.372
Even if I did refuse to do this,

752
00:49:42.573 --> 00:49:44.642
I've never given less than 100 percent.

753
00:49:46.903 --> 00:49:48.013
I know.

754
00:49:50.312 --> 00:49:51.843
Will we have enough time?

755
00:49:56.682 --> 00:49:58.783
We can make our flight if we rush.

756
00:49:59.453 --> 00:50:00.522
Okay.

757
00:50:38.823 --> 00:50:41.593
How about this for your explanation of Mureung City?

758
00:50:51.073 --> 00:50:52.173
What?

759
00:50:53.502 --> 00:50:56.312
You're the first photographer to takes pictures...

760
00:50:57.073 --> 00:50:58.482
with the article in mind.

761
00:51:02.712 --> 00:51:03.783
It's perfect.

762
00:51:06.752 --> 00:51:09.093
- Should we take a few more? - Okay.

763
00:51:11.223 --> 00:51:13.363
She went there for work. What could possibly happen?

764
00:51:13.522 --> 00:51:17.263
She went on multi-day business trips with men, and nothing happened.

765
00:51:17.533 --> 00:51:19.303
What if something happens this time?

766
00:51:19.903 --> 00:51:22.203
You've heard of incidents like that.

767
00:51:22.502 --> 00:51:24.602
You work like crazy and miss the train.

768
00:51:24.803 --> 00:51:27.102
You look for a place to stay, and there's only one.

769
00:51:27.272 --> 00:51:30.412
Furthermore, they have one vacant room.

770
00:51:31.283 --> 00:51:34.653
I hate these cliche and offensive things...

771
00:51:35.182 --> 00:51:36.352
so much.

772
00:51:36.352 --> 00:51:39.883
Why couldn't she come home just because there's no train?

773
00:51:40.582 --> 00:51:43.593
- Right? - Unless there is a rainstorm...

774
00:51:43.852 --> 00:51:44.993
What?

775
00:51:51.703 --> 00:51:52.863
It looks like rain.

776
00:51:53.462 --> 00:51:54.573
Rain?

777
00:51:57.173 --> 00:51:59.002
They can't go anywhere, and it's raining.

778
00:51:59.002 --> 00:52:00.973
Their clothes are drenched, and they become chilly.

779
00:52:01.142 --> 00:52:03.573
And the boiler at the inn is broken.

780
00:52:03.573 --> 00:52:05.182
They need to be in a situation where they can't help...

781
00:52:05.182 --> 00:52:06.783
but share each other's body temperature.

782
00:52:06.783 --> 00:52:10.283
That's when something will finally happen. You know nothing.

783
00:52:13.153 --> 00:52:14.522
I don't even want to think about it.

784
00:52:32.842 --> 00:52:34.242
Our flight got canceled.

785
00:52:35.412 --> 00:52:37.041
The express bus drivers are on a strike,

786
00:52:37.041 --> 00:52:38.642
and the train tickets are all sold out.

787
00:52:41.412 --> 00:52:42.452
What should we do?

788
00:52:44.421 --> 00:52:46.282
We'll just have to borrow the car for a bit longer.

789
00:52:46.751 --> 00:52:48.222
We can't take the plane home anyway.

790
00:52:48.952 --> 00:52:50.521
Do you think we'll be able to go home?

791
00:52:50.762 --> 00:52:53.691
As long as the road doesn't get blocked due to a landslide,

792
00:52:54.021 --> 00:52:55.191
we'll be able to go home.

793
00:52:55.432 --> 00:52:56.662
Don't worry.

794
00:53:02.671 --> 00:53:05.371
We have breaking news. Due to the heavy rain in the southwest,

795
00:53:05.371 --> 00:53:07.811
a landslide has occurred in Mureung City...

796
00:53:08.012 --> 00:53:10.012
which ended up blocking the nearby coastal road.

797
00:53:10.012 --> 00:53:12.742
The authorities have sent people to urgently clear up the road,

798
00:53:12.742 --> 00:53:15.851
and they announced that it'll take around six hours.

799
00:53:15.981 --> 00:53:17.521
We will update you...

800
00:53:17.521 --> 00:53:19.081
- as soon as we hear more. - She can't be there, right?

801
00:53:19.081 --> 00:53:20.581
- We will move onto the next news. - No way.

802
00:53:27.222 --> 00:53:29.461
How is this even possible?

803
00:53:29.992 --> 00:53:32.202
How can this happen?

804
00:53:32.362 --> 00:53:33.862
It's like someone planned this.

805
00:53:34.671 --> 00:53:36.932
Are you saying I planned this?

806
00:53:37.001 --> 00:53:39.371
You were the one who suggested that we should come here.

807
00:53:39.572 --> 00:53:41.612
I knew something was weird when you insisted on...

808
00:53:41.612 --> 00:53:44.941
renting a car just so we could come all the way here.

809
00:53:44.981 --> 00:53:47.211
I can't believe you used the main cut as bait.

810
00:53:47.282 --> 00:53:49.282
It was a great idea. You totally fooled me.

811
00:53:49.782 --> 00:53:51.882
Will you stop talking nonsense?

812
00:53:52.021 --> 00:53:55.392
Then are you saying I caused the landslide?

813
00:53:55.392 --> 00:53:58.222
No, but you could've seen the weather forecast.

814
00:53:58.621 --> 00:54:01.961
Isn't it more plausible to say you created this scenario?

815
00:54:02.561 --> 00:54:06.101
No, I'm very up to date when it comes to romance.

816
00:54:06.302 --> 00:54:08.671
This kind of stuff doesn't even happen in dramas.

817
00:54:09.072 --> 00:54:11.671
This kind of scenario is for people who are lame...

818
00:54:11.671 --> 00:54:13.171
just like you.

819
00:54:13.401 --> 00:54:14.512
What? "Lame"?

820
00:54:14.811 --> 00:54:16.342
Are you seriously going to blame it on me?

821
00:54:16.342 --> 00:54:18.081
We'll soon find out.

822
00:54:18.481 --> 00:54:20.311
You just wait and see.

823
00:54:20.311 --> 00:54:22.882
We'll end up going to a bed and breakfast...

824
00:54:22.882 --> 00:54:24.552
that's run by an old lady.

825
00:54:26.822 --> 00:54:28.592
(Bed and Breakfast)

826
00:54:28.592 --> 00:54:29.851
Hello?

827
00:54:31.521 --> 00:54:32.662
Is anyone here?

828
00:54:33.662 --> 00:54:36.262
Is this the only place you could find?

829
00:54:36.262 --> 00:54:39.561
You saw the map as well. This was the only bed and breakfast.

830
00:54:39.762 --> 00:54:41.901
Exactly. It's weird that you drove to a place...

831
00:54:41.901 --> 00:54:45.142
where there's only one bed and breakfast.

832
00:54:49.342 --> 00:54:50.512
Is no one here?

833
00:54:51.142 --> 00:54:52.581
Are you here...

834
00:54:53.441 --> 00:54:56.851
to stay the night?

835
00:54:59.021 --> 00:55:00.581
Yes, we're here to stay the night.

836
00:55:02.521 --> 00:55:04.862
I bet she'll say there's only one room left.

837
00:55:04.862 --> 00:55:06.961
There are three rooms.

838
00:55:08.231 --> 00:55:10.461
But do you only need one room?

839
00:55:12.561 --> 00:55:14.771
You can rent an entire annex.

840
00:55:15.972 --> 00:55:18.001
We'll... We'll pay for the annex.

841
00:55:18.001 --> 00:55:20.101
We'll take a room each.

842
00:55:20.302 --> 00:55:22.912
And she'll even use the extra room.

843
00:55:23.642 --> 00:55:26.412
We'll sleep separately...

844
00:55:26.412 --> 00:55:28.182
and make sure we don't even touch.

845
00:55:30.151 --> 00:55:33.751
Do as you wish.

846
00:55:34.121 --> 00:55:35.751
Okay. Thank you.

847
00:55:36.092 --> 00:55:37.092
Thank you.

848
00:55:42.061 --> 00:55:44.632
I guess we need to use that to cook our own rice.

849
00:55:44.632 --> 00:55:45.932
I guess so.

850
00:55:45.961 --> 00:55:48.871
But do you think you can sleep here?

851
00:55:49.271 --> 00:55:50.901
I'll just sleep in the car.

852
00:55:51.601 --> 00:55:54.171
- No, I'll sleep in the car. - Here.

853
00:55:56.211 --> 00:55:57.941
You can change into this.

854
00:55:59.382 --> 00:56:00.811
Okay.

855
00:56:01.552 --> 00:56:02.782
You're so kind.

856
00:56:04.351 --> 00:56:05.481
We'll get changed.

857
00:56:09.322 --> 00:56:11.822
- The phone is turned off. - Ha Ri isn't home yet.

858
00:56:12.592 --> 00:56:13.722
Her phone's turned off as well.

859
00:56:13.722 --> 00:56:16.432
She told me she's low on battery. She can't come home tonight.

860
00:56:16.592 --> 00:56:17.731
She's going to sleep outside?

861
00:56:18.702 --> 00:56:20.302
She's with Mr. Han, isn't she?

862
00:56:21.271 --> 00:56:24.572
Are you going to let your daughter spend the night with a guy?

863
00:56:24.742 --> 00:56:26.972
You should go there and drag her home.

864
00:56:27.811 --> 00:56:30.412
I'm actually glad that my daughter's spending the night with a guy.

865
00:56:30.941 --> 00:56:32.541
What kind of guy is he?

866
00:56:32.742 --> 00:56:34.811
Is he normal? How old is he? Does he have his own house?

867
00:56:34.811 --> 00:56:35.851
Is he diligent?

868
00:56:38.282 --> 00:56:41.121
He doesn't own anything, and he's very old.

869
00:56:41.351 --> 00:56:44.222
On top of that, he looks very scary. He has really dark skin.

870
00:56:45.362 --> 00:56:47.162
He's a weirdo. I don't like him.

871
00:56:47.992 --> 00:56:49.932
Then why don't you marry Ha Ri?

872
00:56:52.662 --> 00:56:55.702
I'm just worried about her like an older brother.

873
00:56:55.702 --> 00:56:56.871
Don't take it out on me.

874
00:56:58.101 --> 00:57:00.541
An older brother, my foot. You were born a month later.

875
00:57:00.702 --> 00:57:04.271
Wait until she comes home. I'll teach that brat a lesson.

876
00:57:07.882 --> 00:57:09.552
The phone doesn't work here.

877
00:58:07.771 --> 00:58:11.081
I Sang, you're like a country boy.

878
00:58:11.142 --> 00:58:12.782
What are you talking about?

879
00:58:13.081 --> 00:58:16.012
People think I'm from abroad. They call me Kevin.

880
00:58:16.751 --> 00:58:17.822
Daniel.

881
00:58:18.021 --> 00:58:19.081
Sure.

882
00:58:28.892 --> 00:58:31.302
Why are you burning firewood?

883
00:58:31.961 --> 00:58:33.802
We have a stove.

884
00:58:35.671 --> 00:58:39.072
It's an induction stove. Is that why you couldn't find it?

885
00:58:40.802 --> 00:58:42.371
We saw an iron cauldron.

886
00:58:43.371 --> 00:58:45.012
I put that there to make the place look nice.

887
00:58:49.952 --> 00:58:51.521
Did you cook rice?

888
00:58:51.751 --> 00:58:53.621
We provide meals for our guests.

889
00:58:53.851 --> 00:58:56.452
We bring it all the way to your room like a hotel room service.

890
00:58:57.961 --> 00:59:01.132
You guys are very old-fashioned.

891
00:59:09.901 --> 00:59:11.501
It's nice and warm.

892
00:59:13.202 --> 00:59:15.512
Here's your coffee.

893
00:59:16.171 --> 00:59:17.472
- Thank you. - No problem.

894
00:59:18.882 --> 00:59:20.382
I've never had coffee in a bowl.

895
00:59:21.211 --> 00:59:22.452
Bowl coffee.

896
00:59:26.651 --> 00:59:30.421
I Sang, how did you end up doing photography?

897
00:59:31.362 --> 00:59:34.691
My dad used to enjoy taking photos.

898
00:59:35.132 --> 00:59:36.831
I used to follow my dad to the photo studio...

899
00:59:36.831 --> 00:59:38.532
every time he went there to get his photos printed out.

900
00:59:38.932 --> 00:59:41.061
Then I'd follow him again once the photos were ready.

901
00:59:41.632 --> 00:59:43.271
I enjoyed doing that.

902
00:59:44.941 --> 00:59:47.441
I guess that's why your photos are always so warm.

903
00:59:52.311 --> 00:59:54.282
Your photos are just like you.

904
00:59:58.722 --> 01:00:01.452
Back in the past, we had to wait...

905
01:00:01.452 --> 01:00:03.052
until the photos came out.

906
01:00:03.952 --> 01:00:06.492
It was exciting to wait for them.

907
01:00:07.421 --> 01:00:09.731
It's just like how I can't wait to find out...

908
01:00:10.162 --> 01:00:11.932
what will happen tomorrow.

909
01:00:15.032 --> 01:00:17.171
I'm more curious about today.

910
01:00:20.101 --> 01:00:23.512
I wonder how we'll end up spending the night together.

911
01:00:52.871 --> 01:00:54.271
It's good, right?

912
01:01:06.921 --> 01:01:08.691
- Are you done washing up? - Yes.

913
01:01:08.851 --> 01:01:10.892
Well, I was just about to wash up myself.

914
01:01:11.561 --> 01:01:12.561
I see.

915
01:01:14.222 --> 01:01:16.162
Do they have hot water?

916
01:01:16.532 --> 01:01:18.132
Yes, lots of it.

917
01:01:19.331 --> 01:01:21.802
Right. Good night then.

918
01:01:23.001 --> 01:01:25.142
- Good night. - You too.

919
01:03:13.682 --> 01:03:19.382
(Mr. Han, are you awake?)

920
01:03:22.851 --> 01:03:24.222
(Mr. Han, are you awake?)

921
01:04:47.342 --> 01:04:48.612
Mr. Han!

922
01:04:50.041 --> 01:04:51.512
What are you doing over there?

923
01:05:05.822 --> 01:05:06.892
What is it?

924
01:05:07.862 --> 01:05:08.961
Just a second.

925
01:05:11.362 --> 01:05:13.862
Why are you whispering?

926
01:05:26.711 --> 01:05:27.811
Wait.

927
01:05:41.532 --> 01:05:42.632
This looks so cool.

928
01:06:04.481 --> 01:06:06.151
Gosh, the wind.

929
01:06:08.492 --> 01:06:09.992
My hair's all over the place.

930
01:06:14.561 --> 01:06:16.762
- What a windy day. - What?

931
01:06:24.532 --> 01:06:27.941
Being a big guy, I'm sure you can block the wind for me...

932
01:08:10.371 --> 01:08:12.111
(The herbal infertility treatment introduced in the first episode...)

933
01:08:12.111 --> 01:08:14.182
(was only fabricated for the purpose of the show.)

934
01:08:14.281 --> 01:08:17.152
(Oh My Baby)

935
01:08:17.152 --> 01:08:18.722
You spend the night with him,

936
01:08:18.722 --> 01:08:20.652
but you're telling me you are in a meeting?

937
01:08:20.852 --> 01:08:21.951
Sorry about that.

938
01:08:21.951 --> 01:08:23.951
Why are you apologizing? It's even more annoying.

939
01:08:23.951 --> 01:08:25.421
You need to be wise when choosing men.

940
01:08:25.421 --> 01:08:27.961
Don't be swooned by what you see on the outside.

941
01:08:27.961 --> 01:08:30.092
- You... - I don't need you to protect me.

942
01:08:30.291 --> 01:08:32.562
I'm 39, not 19.

943
01:08:32.632 --> 01:08:34.632
Shouldn't you explain yourself?

944
01:08:34.632 --> 01:08:37.302
I'll start by saying we live under the same roof.

945
01:08:37.302 --> 01:08:39.701
Being this small should be a crime since it makes you...

946
01:08:39.701 --> 01:08:41.642
snugly fit in my embrace.

947
01:08:42.972 --> 01:08:44.342
How do you think of me as a woman?

948
01:08:46.342 --> 01:08:47.411
What?

